==English==

===Etymology===
Named after the industrial chemist Ernst Büchner.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{lb|en|chemistry}} A type of glass [[flask]] used in a [[laboratory]] similar to an [[Erlenmeyer flask]], but with a side spout used for connection to an [[aspirator]].

